all.Name: Espskär 10 pegs in solid ash
all.Body:
Espskär is a simple, somewhat Shaker-style wooden wall-mounted coat rack. It was originally designed by Architect Kristian Gullichsen for his own summer cottage in the Finnish archipelago; a simple and modest house with Japanese influences that represents the tradition of reduced Finnish summer dwelling at its most beautiful. The Espskär coat racks are produced in solid ash and birch.

espskar-coat-rack.Name: Espskär 12 pegs in solid ash
espskar-coat-rack.Body:
Espskär is a simple, somewhat Shaker-style wooden wall-mounted coat rack. It was originally designed by Architect Kristian Gullichsen for his own summer cottage in the Finnish archipelago; a simple and modest house with Japanese influences that represents the tradition of reduced Finnish summer dwelling at its most beautiful. The Espskär coat racks are produced in solid ash and birch. 

 

Dimensions: w 1475 d 76 h 36

Espskär is a simple, somewhat Shaker-style wooden wall-mounted coat rack. The Espskär coat racks are produced in solid ash and birch. 

 

Dimensions: w 225 d 76 h 36

Espskär is a simple, somewhat Shaker-style wooden wall-mounted coat rack. It was originally designed by Architect Kristian Gullichsen for his own summer cottage in the Finnish archipelago; a simple and modest house with Japanese influences that represents the tradition of reduced Finnish summer dwelling at its most beautiful. The Espskär coat racks are produced in solid ash and birch.
